11:10.302 --> 11:11.570
Yeah, I'm not a fan.

11:14.240 --> 11:16.308
Just shut the door on your way out.

11:16.375 --> 11:17.710
Locks automatically.

12:07.560 --> 12:08.527
You are?

12:09.829 --> 12:11.630
Rosen. Rosen, Casey Rosen.

12:11.697 --> 12:12.665
I'm...

12:13.199 --> 12:15.301
I'm in room 406.
I'm just a neighbor.

12:18.938 --> 12:19.939
Neighbor,

12:20.673 --> 12:23.442
you borrow butter, sugar, feed the fish?

12:23.943 --> 12:26.412
Yeah, yeah, you know, stuff like that.
I...

12:27.246 --> 12:29.915
I lent her my vacuum cleaner
a couple of times.

12:29.982 --> 12:31.450
You know she's a simulate?

12:33.319 --> 12:34.386
A simulate?

12:37.690 --> 12:39.091
No, I didn't. I didn't...

12:40.426 --> 12:41.460
Are you sure?

12:41.994 --> 12:43.929
Read the badge, buddy.
I think I'd know.

12:43.996 --> 12:45.431
Right, yeah, yeah. Sorry.

12:46.432 --> 12:47.833
Been offline three years.

12:49.435 --> 12:51.203
I didn't mean to barge in
on you like that.

12:51.270 --> 12:52.838
I saw the tape and the open door.

12:52.905 --> 12:55.608
I just wanted to make sure
everything was okay.

12:56.575 --> 12:57.576
I see.

12:58.110 --> 12:59.111
Keep talking.

13:00.146 --> 13:02.314
Thanks. Yeah, that's, that's Trotsky.

13:07.653 --> 13:10.656
Well, you know where to find me
if you need anything.

13:11.390 --> 13:12.391
Yep.

13:13.526 --> 13:14.527
Come on, boy.

13:50.462 --> 13:53.232
So, I made us a reservation tonight
at Papillon.

13:55.434 --> 13:57.469
I thought Lisa would cook for us.

13:57.536 --> 13:59.305
Baby, I need a night out. Okay?

13:59.371 --> 14:01.740
We need a night out together.

14:02.541 --> 14:05.177
Okay, but not Papillon.

14:05.244 --> 14:07.179
Fine. Anywhere, okay?
Just...

14:07.246 --> 14:09.915
I mean, obviously somewhere nice.
But anywhere.

14:09.982 --> 14:11.317
-Okay.
-Okay.

14:33.138 --> 14:34.073
Analyzing.

14:38.210 --> 14:40.212
AICE, Artificial Intelligence...

14:40.279 --> 14:41.814
Shouldn't you be at home, convalescing?

14:41.880 --> 14:43.915
I'm fine. This thing
just banged me up a little.

14:43.983 --> 14:46.085
Well, you must be frightened too
'cause you shut down

14:46.151 --> 14:47.886
the power
to an entire city block.

14:47.953 --> 14:51.156
You're only supposed to let off
an EMP that size in an emergency.

14:51.223 --> 14:53.025
The sim able to assault
a civilian with intent.

14:53.092 --> 14:55.728
I think that's an emergency, don't you?
This thing ignored straight commands.

14:55.794 --> 14:57.296
It didn't even shut down when I asked.

14:57.363 --> 14:58.831
You know,
it asked me if I was okay after,

14:58.897 --> 15:00.399
like it had some kind of empathy.

15:00.466 --> 15:02.701
I went into where it lives, right?

15:02.768 --> 15:04.903
And there was a level of awareness
there like I've never seen.

15:04.970 --> 15:07.273
It had a handwritten diary filled
with intimate thoughts

15:07.339 --> 15:09.341
and a sketchbook, alright,
with beautiful pictures.

15:09.408 --> 15:10.576
One of them was with his neighbor.

15:10.643 --> 15:12.211
And I think we need to go back
and talk to him.

15:12.278 --> 15:13.912
Is the sim registered to him?

15:14.313 --> 15:15.948
-No.
-Well then, leave him alone.

15:16.015 --> 15:17.349
Just let me investigate.

15:17.916 --> 15:19.385
Look, we got plenty to do.

15:19.885 --> 15:21.153
Why don't you just go home?

15:21.220 --> 15:22.221
I'm telling you,

15:22.688 --> 15:23.822
this one's different.

15:24.790 --> 15:25.858
Debug complete.

15:26.392 --> 15:27.993
Abnormalities detected.

15:28.060 --> 15:29.928
Restriction definitions altered.

15:30.296 --> 15:31.530
Precepts affected.

15:34.533 --> 15:35.768
Hey, I was never here.

15:37.303 --> 15:39.571
I think you need to learn

15:39.638 --> 15:41.974
how to take care of another life form.

15:42.040 --> 15:43.509
So, what happened here?

15:43.575 --> 15:44.910
The sim has been hacked.

15:45.277 --> 15:47.246
Somebody altered the restrictions.

15:47.313 --> 15:50.115
They redefined words like harm,
modify, obey,

15:50.182 --> 15:54.720
and then negated the sentiment analysis
of the other precepts to nullify them.

15:56.088 --> 15:58.290
So, someone made it possible
for it to hurt me.

15:58.357 --> 16:00.459
The precepts are designed to protect us.

16:00.526 --> 16:03.362
But some forms of harm are subject
to the interpretation

16:03.429 --> 16:05.297
of the individual experiencing it.

16:05.831 --> 16:08.300
In order for sims to function,
there has to be nuances

16:08.367 --> 16:11.003
-in the definition of the restrictions.
-Yeah.

16:11.637 --> 16:14.873
-Slow, slow down.
-The hacker gave it complete autonomy.

16:16.375 --> 16:17.309
Freeze that.

16:20.446 --> 16:21.780
That guy's her neighbor.

16:23.282 --> 16:24.216
What?

16:25.217 --> 16:26.752
He's all over its memories.

16:31.457 --> 16:34.827
Call Nexxera and ask if they ever had
a Casey Rosen working for them.

16:34.893 --> 16:35.828
Okay.

16:36.095 --> 16:38.063
You want me to do a full wipe,
all the auction desk,

16:38.130 --> 16:39.365
send it back to market?

16:39.431 --> 16:40.799
No, no, let's just...

16:42.167 --> 16:43.836
just see how dangerous it is.

16:45.537 --> 16:46.805
Who did this to you?

16:49.742 --> 16:51.610
At Nexxera, the future is forever.

16:51.677 --> 16:53.712
Come on, man, just let me in.

16:53.779 --> 16:54.847
There's nothing in there.

16:54.913 --> 16:56.181
He moved out.
When?

16:56.248 --> 16:57.182
Yesterday.

16:59.284 --> 17:01.553
-Where to?
-I don't know. I didn't ask.

17:01.620 --> 17:03.822
Well, just let me in Casey's apartment.

17:12.030 --> 17:13.999
Search Nexxera database.

17:15.233 --> 17:16.969
Casey Rosen.

17:17.403 --> 17:18.337
Searching.

17:19.605 --> 17:20.571
No results.

17:51.303 --> 17:52.404
New message.

17:53.338 --> 17:54.306
Hey.

17:54.706 --> 17:57.976
I just wanted to tell you I met
with that lawyer today,

17:58.043 --> 18:01.046
the one that specializes
in simulate neglect cases.

18:02.147 --> 18:04.383
There are other parents coming forward.

18:04.783 --> 18:05.751
So,

18:06.752 --> 18:08.921
looks like we don't have to do this...

18:11.857 --> 18:14.193
Do you dream of a lifelong companion?

18:14.259 --> 18:17.496
Simulates are as close to human
as humanly possible.

18:17.996 --> 18:20.632
At Nexxera, the future is forever.

18:22.267 --> 18:24.136
-Looking to sell?
-Yeah, come here, come here.

18:24.203 --> 18:25.170
Alright.

18:25.637 --> 18:28.874
I need every detail you got
on the guy you sold this to.

18:28.941 --> 18:31.477
Okay, those books are rare.
That information is protected.

18:31.543 --> 18:34.179
I'd be breaking the law if I give
that to you.

18:34.580 --> 18:37.149
Yeah, but this is fake, man. Yeah?

18:37.583 --> 18:40.118
You running
a little black market scam here.

18:40.752 --> 18:41.854
This guy, right?

18:41.920 --> 18:43.455
His name is Casey Rosen.

18:43.522 --> 18:47.092
Alright? He looks like this.
He's got tattoos though. Alright?

18:49.027 --> 18:50.329
That's not Casey Rosen.

18:51.897 --> 18:52.931
That's Desmond Han.

18:53.699 --> 18:54.633
Who?

18:55.367 --> 18:56.368
Desmond Han.

19:00.038 --> 19:01.106
Freeze!

19:42.314 --> 19:43.248
Meshiagare.

19:45.217 --> 19:47.152
I think maybe we could use a fork.

19:49.154 --> 19:50.088
I'll be fine.

20:50.649 --> 20:51.950
I had that dream again.

20:56.355 --> 20:57.856
Okay, let's go inside.

20:59.358 --> 21:01.159
-It's not a bad idea.
-Okay.

21:02.160 --> 21:03.562
Okay, I'm not saying yes.

21:03.895 --> 21:04.863
-Yet.
-But

21:05.197 --> 21:07.432
just explain it to me one more time.

21:07.966 --> 21:09.034
Okay,

21:09.101 --> 21:10.068
we activate them.

21:10.602 --> 21:12.137
And now, they're us.

21:12.204 --> 21:13.972
-They live long.
-No, no, no, no,

21:14.039 --> 21:15.741
our love lives live on.

21:19.011 --> 21:23.115
I mean, by the time we die, I'm
sure they'll just plop our brains and...

22:02.988 --> 22:03.989
Stop.

22:07.325 --> 22:08.260
What's wrong?

22:12.964 --> 22:13.899
You okay?

22:23.775 --> 22:24.910
What is it?

22:26.978 --> 22:28.613
I have to tell you something.

22:30.882 --> 22:31.817
Anything.

22:40.325 --> 22:41.259
Come.

22:54.106 --> 22:55.307
I'm so sorry.

23:00.045 --> 23:01.146
What are you doing?

23:08.653 --> 23:09.588
No.

23:11.923 --> 23:12.858
No.

23:29.708 --> 23:31.476
Evan died in a coma.

23:31.543 --> 23:32.511
No.

23:32.978 --> 23:33.945
I'm Evan.

23:35.013 --> 23:36.214
We got you before.

23:37.249 --> 23:38.350
We both got one.

23:42.220 --> 23:43.588
I thought you would help.

24:17.455 --> 24:19.257
Why are you showing me this now?

24:25.230 --> 24:27.032
Because I can't do this anymore.

24:36.541 --> 24:38.343
I grant you access to this room.

24:55.894 --> 24:56.895
You were here.

25:01.132 --> 25:02.133
We just

25:04.569 --> 25:05.570
lie down,

25:06.972 --> 25:08.573
relax, and remember.

25:10.075 --> 25:11.943
What? They capture our memories?

25:13.678 --> 25:14.779
Our thoughts.

25:15.413 --> 25:17.749
We can erase things,
but they say not to.

25:18.583 --> 25:19.651
Can she hear us?

25:20.819 --> 25:21.920
No.

25:21.987 --> 25:25.290
She's only to store information
right now, not process it.

25:38.570 --> 25:40.438
Why can't I remember any of this?

25:43.008 --> 25:44.209
I had it erased.

25:47.245 --> 25:48.446
Shit.

25:48.513 --> 25:49.481
Shut down.

25:51.516 --> 25:52.550
Welcome.

25:53.151 --> 25:54.085
Thank you.

26:02.761 --> 26:04.496
This is the service man, Ms. Aline.

26:04.562 --> 26:05.530
Mr. Rosen.

26:05.964 --> 26:06.998
Casey, please.

26:07.866 --> 26:08.967
I'm sorry, did...

26:09.567 --> 26:10.669
did you paint this?

26:11.036 --> 26:12.070
Yes.

26:13.338 --> 26:14.773
It's... it's incredible.

26:15.840 --> 26:18.610
I love what you've done
with the colors. It's...

26:18.677 --> 26:19.644
just magnificent.

26:21.346 --> 26:22.347
Thank you.

26:22.814 --> 26:23.915
It's right this way.

26:24.883 --> 26:25.850
Yes, yes.

